==English==

===Verb===
'''[[get]] [[it]]'''

# ''literal:'' To [[get]], [[retrieve]], or [[receive]] something.
#:''If you order the pizza, I'll go '''get it'''.''
# {{idiom}} To [[understand]], [[comprehend]], or [[grasp]].
#:''If they don't '''get it''', explain it a different way.''
# {{idiom}} To realize why a [[joke]] is [[funny]].
#:''I thought it was hilarious, but she didn't '''get it'''.''
# ''Figurative:'' To feel one's [[wrath]], or receive punishment.
#:''After the way she spoke to him, she's really going to '''get it''' this time.''

